 pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-625_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-626_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-628_">Can lavender essential oil be used during pregnancy?</span></h3><div data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-evcjhq dAUdgU pf-629_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-d2fd0d62--Pregnancy_1200x.jpg?v=1607712880" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-d2fd0d62--Pregnancy.jpg?v=1607712880 1536w" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy"/></div><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-630_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-632_">Lavender is one of the most well-known as well as one of the most researched essential oils due to its popularity and wide range of benefits.<br><br>The general consensus is that lavender essential oil is safe to use during pregnancy. In fact, a study was conducted in 2016 which concluded that lavender essential oil could help to reduce labour pains and aid relaxation during childbirth.<br><br>If you choose to use lavender essential oil during your pregnancy or birth, there are many ways in which you can do this. One of the most common ways is to add a few drops to a diffuser, allowing the aroma to fill the room. Alternatively, you could add a few drops of lavender oil to a carrier oil such as jojoba oil or sweet almond oil and ask your birth partner to massage it into your back.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-4283" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bQtKYq fbyRgD pf-633_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-jHkVzv dyVEVs"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-634_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-635_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-636_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-637_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-638_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-640_">Can lavender essential oil be used on children?</span></h3><div data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-evcjhq dAUdgU pf-641_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-f774f5a3--baby_1200x.jpg?v=1607716572" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-f774f5a3--baby.jpg?v=1607716572 1536w" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy"/></div><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-bilyIR cCHonK pf-642_"><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-643_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-645_">Lavender essential oil is safe for use on children. However, when it comes to using lavender essential oil with children, a little goes a long way.
<br><br>Some of the ways in which lavender oil can be used with children include:
</span></p></div><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-FNXRL lgZllt pf-646_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jWUzzU hBMhiW pf-647_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-649_">üíú&nbsp; &nbsp;Adding lavender oil to a carrier oil and using it as a massage oil. This is a great way to help children relax and can be used before bedtime. However, we'd always recommend using a weaker dilution on children due to their sensitive skin. One drop of lavender oil mixed with a tablespoon of carrier oil should be sufficient.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jWUzzU hBMhiW pf-650_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-652_">üíú&nbsp; &nbsp;Diffusing lavender oil in an essential oil diffuser. This is a great way to create a calming environment for children.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jWUzzU hBMhiW pf-653_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-655_">üíú&nbsp; &nbsp;Adding lavender oil to a bathtub of water. This is a relaxing way to use lavender oil and can be especially helpful for children with anxiety or who are struggling to sleep. Don't forget to mix the essential oil with a carrier oil before adding it to the bath water, as this helps the oil to disperse through the water.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jWUzzU hBMhiW pf-656_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-658_">üíú&nbsp; &nbsp;Create a relaxing pillow mist to use at bedtime. To do this, fill a clean spray bottle with distilled water and add a few drops of lavender essential oil. Then, spray your child's pillow and bedding with the mixture to help them to fall asleep at night.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9e91" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bQtKYq fbyRgD pf-659_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-jHkVzv dyVEVs"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-660_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-p